<subSubSection id="20EBE9A29F351C2EFF5061717EF73C6B" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="684EBA299F351C2EFF5061717EF73C6B" blockId="27.[151,1437,364,535]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFF5061717C5A3FFA" bold="true" box="[151,274,364,391]" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFE7E61707F553FFA" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[441,541,365,391]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFE7E61707F553FFA" box="[441,541,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFDEB61707F253FFA" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[556,621,365,391]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFDEB61707F253FFA" box="[556,621,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFD6161717E6E3FFB" authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[678,806,364,390]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFD6161717E6E3FFB" box="[678,806,364,390]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the rectangular valvae, the transverse constriction of the bursa and the broad posterior ductus bursae with strong sclerotisation in the ostium area. Distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFAFE618C78D53FD6" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1337,1437,401,427]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFAFE618C78D53FD6" box="[1337,1437,401,427]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFF0161A97C0E3FB3" authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[198,326,436,462]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFF0161A97C0E3FB3" box="[198,326,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the stout tip of the uncus. Further distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFCBF61A97EB03FB3" authority="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas, 2019" authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" box="[888,1016,436,462]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFCBF61A97EB03FB3" box="[888,1016,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Sagarriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the U-shaped saccus, distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFF5061C47DB33F8E" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[151,251,473,499]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFF5061C47DB33F8E" box="[151,251,473,499]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Coscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the cleft tip of the valva and the absence of a sclerotized spiny band traversing the bursa, and distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="AFF1C1AA9F351C2EFF1261E07C5E3C6A" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[213,278,509,535]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A85663B9F351C2EFF1261E07C5E3C6A" box="[213,278,509,535]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="428">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of a clavus on the base of the valva (
<tableCitation id="25738F929F351C2EFC9D61E17EE63C6B" box="[858,942,508,534]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1126,1150]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Overview of compared genitalia features in the investigated genera." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3C8EEAA19F2A1C31FF50647B7EAC3A02" pageId="27" pageNumber="428" tableUuid="3C8EEAA19F2A1C31FF50647B7EAC3A02">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
